trans-unit.source: gedit is the official text editor of the GNOME desktop environment. While aiming at simplicity and ease of use, gedit is a powerful general purpose text editor.
trans-unit.target: gedit is the official text editor of the GNOME desktop environment. While aiming at simplicity and ease of use, gedit is a powerful general purpose text editor.

trans-unit.source: Whether you are writing the next bestseller, programming an innovative application, or simply taking some quick notes, gedit will be a reliable tool to accomplish your task.
trans-unit.target: Whether you are writing the next bestseller, programming an innovative application, or simply taking some quick notes, gedit will be a reliable tool to accomplish your task.

trans-unit.source: Its flexible plugin system allows you to tailor the application to your needs and adapt it to your workflow.
trans-unit.target: Its flexible plugin system allows you to tailor the application to your needs and adapt it to your workflow.

trans-unit.source: Whether to use the system's default fixed width font for editing text instead of a font specific to gedit. If this option is turned off, then the font named in the "Editor Font" option will be used instead of the system font.
trans-unit.target: Whether to use the system's default fixed width font for editing text instead of a font specific to gedit. If this option is turned off, then the font named in the "Editor Font" option will be used instead of the system font.

trans-unit.source: A custom font that will be used for the editing area. This will only take effect if the "Use Default Font" option is turned off.
trans-unit.target: A custom font that will be used for the editing area. This will only take effect if the "Use Default Font" option is turned off.

trans-unit.source: The ID of a GtkSourceView Style Scheme used to color the text.
trans-unit.target: The ID of a GtkSourceView Style Scheme used to color the text.

trans-unit.source: Whether gedit should create backup copies for the files it saves.
trans-unit.target: Whether gedit should create backup copies for the files it saves.

trans-unit.source: Whether gedit should automatically save modified files after a time interval. You can set the time interval with the "Autosave Interval" option.
trans-unit.target: Whether gedit should automatically save modified files after a time interval. You can set the time interval with the "Autosave Interval" option.

trans-unit.source: Number of minutes after which gedit will automatically save modified files. This will only take effect if the "Autosave" option is turned on.
trans-unit.target: Number of minutes after which gedit will automatically save modified files. This will only take effect if the "Autosave" option is turned on.

trans-unit.source: Maximum number of actions that gedit will be able to undo or redo. Use "-1" for unlimited number of actions.
trans-unit.target: Maximum number of actions that gedit will be able to undo or redo. Use "-1" for unlimited number of actions.

trans-unit.source: Specifies how to wrap long lines in the editing area. Use "none" for no wrapping, "word" for wrapping at word boundaries, and "char" for wrapping at individual character boundaries. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
trans-unit.target: Specifies how to wrap long lines in the editing area. Use "none" for no wrapping, "word" for wrapping at word boundaries, and "char" for wrapping at individual character boundaries. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.

trans-unit.target: Last split mode choice for line wrapping mode

trans-unit.source: Specifies the last split mode used with line wrapping mode, so that when wrapping mode is off we still remember the split mode choice. Use "word" for wrapping at word boundaries, and "char" for wrapping at individual character boundaries.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the last split mode used with line wrapping mode, so that when wrapping mode is off we still remember the split mode choice. Use "word" for wrapping at word boundaries, and "char" for wrapping at individual character boundaries.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the number of spaces that should be displayed instead of Tab characters.

trans-unit.source: Whether gedit should insert spaces instead of tabs.

trans-unit.source: Whether gedit should enable automatic indentation.
trans-unit.target: Whether gedit should enable automatic indentation.

trans-unit.source: Whether gedit should display line numbers in the editing area.
trans-unit.target: Whether gedit should display line numbers in the editing area.

trans-unit.source: Whether gedit should highlight the current line.
trans-unit.target: Whether gedit should highlight the current line.

trans-unit.source: Whether gedit should highlight matching brackets.

trans-unit.target: Specifies the position of the right margin.

trans-unit.source: Specifies how the cursor moves when the HOME and END keys are pressed. Use "disabled" to always move at the start/end of the line, "after" to move to the start/end of the line the first time the keys are pressed and to the start/end of the text ignoring whitespaces the second time the keys are pressed, "before" to move to the start/end of the text before moving to the start/end of the line and "always" to always move to the start/end of the text instead of the start/end of the line.
trans-unit.target: Specifies how the cursor moves when the HOME and END keys are pressed. Use "disabled" to always move at the start/end of the line, "after" to move to the start/end of the line the first time the keys are pressed and to the start/end of the text ignoring whitespaces the second time the keys are pressed, "before" to move to the start/end of the text before moving to the start/end of the line and "always" to always move to the start/end of the text instead of the start/end of the line.
